						<summary>

						<p>On the Nandi-pillar set up infront of the Agastyēśvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>KŌMAṬIVĒMA.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1340, Viḷambi, Kārttika, Śu. 11 [Monday] corresponding to October 10, Monday, 1418 A.D. The month being the Adhika Kārttika.</p>						

						<p>Badly damaged. Records a gift of land, house and garden <hi rend="italic">(gṛihārāma-sasyakshētrālu)</hi> by soldiers <hi rend="italic">(ekkaṭīlu) (pampuna)</hi> of Velaṇṭūru, on behalf of (paṁpuna) Kōmaṭivēmaṇḍalēśvara to the god Kēśavarāya.</p>						

						</summary>
